comment: Bradley (BOS) makes contact with the arm and body of Jackson (DET) as he attempts to reach in for the steal.
Pressey (BOS) makes contact with Jackson's (DET) wrist, affecting his shot attempt.
Prince (DET) and Olynyk (BOS) briefly engage, but let go and do not affect each other's ability to contest the rebound.
RHH shows Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes contact with Crowder's (BOS) body and arm during his shot attempt.
RHH shows Jackson (DET) gather the ball while on his right foot. He then lands on his left foot first, establishing his pivot. He may move his right foot as many times as he wants.
Wallace (BOS) dislodges Jackson (DET) and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
RHH shows Turner (BOS) loses control of the ball as he rises up for the jumpshot over Jackson (DET).
L-Slash shows Crowder (BOS) hits the ball, causing Prince (DET) to lose it.
Jackson (DET) moves his pivot foot heel to toe as he spins on the perimeter.
Jackson (DET) grabs and holds Turner (BOS) and prevents him from using the screen.
Jerebko (BOS) sets a legal screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET), giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
L-Slash shows Jackson (DET) stick his leg into the path of Zeller (BOS) as he's backing up, causing Zeller to stumble into Caldwell-Pope (DET).
Jackson (DET) grabs Bradley's (BOS) arm and prevents him from playing legal defense.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) cleanly knocks the entry pass intended for Jerebko (BOS) away.
Drummond (DET) grabs and holds the arm of Olynyk (BOS) and prevents him from getting open to catch the inbounds pass.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) does not establish legal guarding position when he makes body to body contact with Crowder (BOS) at the start of his drive.
Olynyk (BOS) establishes himself in the path of Jackson (DET) before the contact.
Bradley (BOS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Jackson (DET) on the perimeter.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) allows Crowder (BOS) to return to the floor and the incidental contact is created by Crowder after the jumpshot.
Turner (BOS) grabs Jackson (DET) from behind after he secures the rebound.
Bradley (BOS) reaches in and makes illegal contact with the arm and body of Jackson (DET) as he defends on the perimeter.
Jerebko (BOS) commits a take foul on Prince (DET)
Turner (BOS) pushes off Jackson (DET) and prevents him from going after the loose ball.
Jerebko (BOS) commits a take foul on Meeks (DET).
Jerebko (BOS) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
Bass (BOS) sets the screen on Jackson (DET), giving him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Turner (BOS) gathers then takes three steps on the drive to the basket.
Tolliver (DET) makes contact with Turner's (BOS) arm and body, affecting his shot attempt.
Turner (BOS) commits a take foul on Caldwell-Pope (DET)
